BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Movie Monday at Portside on Main
DTSTART:20260629T183000
DTEND:20260629T203000
DTSTAMP:20260625T062511Z
UID:gz-movie-monday-at-portside-on-main-1754155@southbaldwinchamber.com
DESCRIPTION:Description\nJoin us this summer for Movie Monday at Portside 
 on Main!\nPresented by\nLiquid Life Vacation Rentals\n\, Movie Monday is a
  free outdoor screening series that’s serving up sunshine\, cinema\, and
  summer fun all season long.\nEach Monday from June 1 through July 27\, ca
 tch a classic family flick under the stars & settle in for a night of laug
 hs\, nostalgia\, and big-screen memories where the smell of salt is in the
  air.\nWhen: Every Monday from June 1 - July 27 from 6:30 - 8:30 pm\nWhere
 : Portside on Main\nCost: Free admission + parking (some activities cost $
 5-10) & Free popcorn from AMC\nEvent Schedule\n6:30 pm: Movie Begins\n8:30
  pm\, 9 pm\, 9:30 pm: SPECTRA Laser Light Experience\nWeekly Movie Schedul
 e\nJune 1: The Parent Trap\nJune 8: The Little Rascals\nJune 15: Dennis th
 e Menace\nJune 22: Free Willy\nJune 29: Remember the Titans\nJuly 6: Angel
 s in the Outfield\nJuly 13: Sing 2\nJuly 20: Clifford the Big Red Dog\nJul
 y 27: Migration\nMake The Wharf your Monday movie destination this summer
 —because great films\, family time\, and coastal nights are the perfect 
 combo.\n\n---\n🌐 View original event: https://businesshub.southbaldwinc
 hamber.com/calendar/Details/movie-monday-at-portside-on-main-1754155
LOCATION:The Wharf\, 23101 Canal Road\, Orange Beach\,\, AL\, 36561\, Unit
 ed States
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:State of A.L.I.C.E. by United Way of Baldwin County
DTSTART:20260630T090000
DTEND:20260630T100000
DTSTAMP:20260625T062511Z
UID:gz-state-of-a-l-i-c-e-by-united-way-of-baldwin-county-1750147@southbal
 dwinchamber.com
DESCRIPTION:Description\nYou're invited!\nA.L.I.C.E. stands for\nAsset Lim
 ited\, Income Constrained\, Employed\n— hardworking individuals and fami
 lies who are struggling to keep up with the rising cost of everyday essent
 ials. In Baldwin County alone\,\n29% of households can’t afford the basi
 cs\n\, and the latest data paints a powerful picture of the challenges fac
 ing our community.\nJoin United Way of Baldwin County for the unveiling of
  the newest ALICE report and gain insight into the real stories behind the
  numbers. This important conversation will explore what the data means for
  Baldwin County’s future — from workforce and housing challenges to ec
 onomic growth and community support — and why it matters to businesses\,
  leaders\, and residents alike.\nRSVP Here!\n\n---\n🌐 View original eve
 nt: https://businesshub.southbaldwinchamber.com/calendar/Details/state-of-
 a-l-i-c-e-by-united-way-of-baldwin-county-1750147
LOCATION:Robertsdale Central Annex\, 22251 Palmer St D\, Robertsdale\,\, A
 L\, 36567\, United States
END:VEVENT
